sentence: Feb 11 (Reuters) - When Idaho nurse Joan West received a fundraising mailer from U.S. Representative Liz Cheney, she saw a way to address her regret for having voted for Donald Trump in 2016 and her worry about the future of U.S. democracy: She wrote a $500 check.
author: Nathan Layne
title: Surge of out-of-state donors boost Trump critic Cheney's campaign -but cannot vote for her

sentence: Former President Donald Trump will address his supporters at an annual meeting of conservative activists in Orlando, Florida, while his Republican critics will hear from the congresswoman he's hellbent on defeating Rep. Liz Cheney, R-Wyo.
title: With Liz Cheney's re-election prospects in doubt, her national profile grows

sentence: WASHINGTON Rep. Liz Cheney, R-Wyo., who has risen to national prominence as one of the most vocal opponents of former President Donald Trump, raised $2.94 million in toward her re-election bid the first quarter of 2022, her campaign confirmed to NBC News on Monday.
title: Cheney capitalizes off national profile to raise $2.9 million in first quarter of 2022
